{"title":"Rally Keystone Token Creation/Validation Concurrencies Usage","type":"markdown","params":{"markdown":"## Using Browbeat Keystone Dashboard

1. Select relevant search terms to **"namespace"** your results
2. Pick time period in top right corner to cover period of time of testing
3. Review results in graphs


## Search Terms
* cloud_name
* version.osp_version
* browbeat_rerun
* browbeat_uuid
* software-metadata.keystone.provider



## Examples
All runs of UUID tokens for OSP10:
* cloud_name: cloud09 AND version.osp_version: 10 AND software-metadata.keystone.provider:\*uuid\*

First rerun of UUID tokens for OSP9:
* cloud_name: cloud09 AND version.osp_version: 9 AND browbeat_rerun: 0 AND software-metadata.keystone.provider:\*uuid\*


Second run of Fernet tokens for OSP10 on specific Browbeat run:
* cloud_name: cloud09 AND version.osp_version: 10 AND browbeat_rerun: 1 AND browbeat_uuid: e6e66688-60d1-4d5d-bb00-7089b3b4d32f AND software-metadata.keystone.provider:\*fernet\*"},"aggs":[],"listeners":{}}
